---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { rel, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../consts';
const description = 'Support and contact for Dudley Development apps — Powell Prowl: Rate Chase and Vibe Rater.';
---
<Base title="Support" description={description} path="/support">
  <main class="page">
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width:720px;">
      <a class="back" href={rel('/')}>← Home</a>
      <h1>Support</h1>
      <p class="updated">We read every message.</p>

      <p>
        Need help with a Dudley app? Email us and we'll chase it down. Please include your device and
        iOS version (Settings → General → About), which app and screen, and what happened — a screenshot
        or recording helps.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a class="btn primary" href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}?subject=Dudley%20Development%20Support`}>Email Support</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Powell Prowl: Rate Chase</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>The game is stuck on a level / something broke.</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">Tap the gear icon (top-right of the home screen) → Settings → <em>Reset all progress</em>. That clears saved state, unlock progress, and tutorial flags. Force-quit the app and reopen.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>How do I unlock the later levels?</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">Beat each level to unlock the next, all the way to Level 31. The curve gets tight on Hard — drop to Easy in Settings for a more forgiving ride.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>My Game Center score isn't showing.</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">Make sure you're signed into Game Center: iOS Settings → Game Center → sign in with your Apple ID, then open the app → Settings → Leaderboards. If you're not signed in, scores still save locally but won't post publicly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Can I turn off sound or haptics?</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">Yes. Gear icon → Settings → Audio &amp; Feel. Sound effects, music, and haptics each toggle independently.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Is this endorsing or attacking a real person?</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">No. It's a parody with fictional caricatures, in the tradition of satirical comedy. The app makes no political statement or endorsement.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Vibe Rater</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Is the rating real?</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">Vibe Rater is for entertainment. It's a playful, for-fun take on your photo's "vibe" — not a measurement of anything real about you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>Where do my photos go?</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">Nowhere. Photos you pick are processed on your device and are not uploaded to us. See the <a href={rel('/privacy/vibe-rater')}>Vibe Rater privacy policy</a> for details.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <strong>The phone vibrates while it analyzes — is that a bug?</strong>
        <p style="margin:6px 0 0;">Nope, that's the joke. It's a Vibe <em>Rater</em>, so it vibrates. You can mute haptics in Settings.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Still need a hand?</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a> and we'll get back to you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
